From: Zhong Hongbo <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jan 2014 16:17:10 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 0384/1072] ARM: 7908/1: mm: Fix the arm_dma_limit calculation

commit: 787b0d5c1ca7ff24feb6f92e4c7f4410ee7d81a8 upstream

Current code is using PHYS_OFFSET to calculate the arm_dma_limit which
will lead to wrong calculations in cases where PHYS_OFFSET is updated
runtime.

So fix the code by using __pv_phys_offset instead of PHYS_OFFSET.

Cc: Catalin Marinas <catalin.marinas@arm.com>
Cc: Nicolas Pitre <nicolas.pitre@linaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Santosh Shilimkar <santosh.shilimkar@ti.com>
Signed-off-by: Russell King <rmk+kernel@arm.linux.org.uk>
Signed-off-by: Hongbo Zhong <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mm/init.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mm/init.c b/arch/arm/mm/init.c
index dd5d5ae..dc89501 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mm/init.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mm/init.c
@@ -236,7 +236,7 @@ void __init setup_dma_zone(struct machine_desc *mdesc)
 #ifdef CONFIG_ZONE_DMA
 	if (mdesc->dma_zone_size) {
 		arm_dma_zone_size = mdesc->dma_zone_size;
-		arm_dma_limit = PHYS_OFFSET + arm_dma_zone_size - 1;
+		arm_dma_limit = __pv_phys_offset + arm_dma_zone_size - 1;
 	} else
 		arm_dma_limit = 0xffffffff;
 #endif
